FBIS3-26095 "drchi023_k_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Feb 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Deng Yingchao's Birthday Commemorated in Beijing Li Ruihuan Addresses Forum OW0202150694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1455 GMT 2 Feb 94 OW0202150694 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, February 2 (XINHUA) -- A forum was held here today to mark the 90th birth anniversary of Deng Yingchao, wife of the late Premier Zhou Enlai, and the publication of her writings. Speaking at the forum, Li Ruihuan, a Standing Committee member of the Communist Party's Politburo, praised Deng as an outstanding woman of the Chinese nation and a world-renowned stateswoman and social activist. While serving as chairwoman of the Sixth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), Deng Yingchao, who died in 1992, upheld and improved the system of multi-party cooperation and political consultation under the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party, said Li, who is also chairman of the CPPCC National Committee. Also speaking at the forum, Huang Qizao, vice-president of the All-China Women's Federation, described Deng Yingchao as a pioneer and leader of the the Chinese women's movement. Deng mobilized and organized women to participate in revolutionary movements, production and economic construction, she said. Deng also appealed for the realization of the equality of men and women legally and in real life, and repeatedly emphasized the need to protect women's fundamental interests through legislation. Furthermore, Deng urged government bodies at all levels to pay close attention to the training and promotion of women officials, Huang said, noting: "She was an outstanding representative of the new breed of women brought up in the Chinese people's revolutionary cause."
